a1dc15;02/08/2020 00:30:00;February 15, 2020;W. R. Berkley Corporation;Las Vegas, NV;Sales;Claims Representative;filter_3;v;claims-representative-a1dc15;v;<p> <p> <b>  Company Details </b> </p> </p>  <p> <b> What we are looking for?.</b> </p> <p> BerkleyNet is a workers compensation insurance company that is committed to making things easy- and doing it all online. We have created a team of open-minded innovators who deliver BerkleyNet?s signature phrase; ridiculously fast and amazingly easy service. At BerkleyNet, we fearlessly explore new paths and share our knowledge to grow our team. BerkleyNet is constantly challenging the status quo and is looking for courageous troubleshooters to help us excel! </p> <p> We are searching for an individual to join our team of curious negotiators as a Claims Trainee. In this role, you will collaborate with a fantastic team to provide world-class claim management and managed care solutions. As Claims Trainee, you will use your curious mindset to investigate claims and negotiate the best outcome for both sides. At BerkleyNet, the Claims team?s successes are integral to our success. If you want to make a difference in this company please consider applying today!</p> <p> <b> A day in the life at BerkleyNet:</b> </p> <li> Research, learn, and apply worker's compensation statutes</li> <li> Investigate claims as reported and determine eligibility for benefits and administer benefits as warranted</li> <li> Address client issues and respond to inquiries promptly</li> <li> Manage the progression of the claims process through collaboration with physicians, nurses, attorneys and other parties as needed</li> <li> Analyze and process claims with the ability to have ownership of policy and claim transactions</li> <li> Translate data and understand department processes, functionality and requirements</li> <li> Maintain compliance with federal and state regulations</li> <li> Must be able to work independently and within a team environment</li> <li> Performs other related duties as required and assigned</li> <p> <b> Qualifications</b> </p> <li> Must possess a Bachelor?s Degree or equivalent work experience (business law/risk management degree preferred)</li> <li> Ability to maintain a current adjuster license</li> <li> Possess strong quantitative, analytical and problem-solving skills</li> <li> Ability to understand department processes, functionality and requirements</li> <li> Must be customer focused, have a great phone presence, courteous and exercise good judgment</li> <li> Must have excellent verbal and written communication and interpersonal skills</li> <li> Great organization and time management skills with the ability to handle and adhere to team schedule</li> <li> Experience in insurance industry or claims management preferred</li> <li> Exposure to vendor management preferred </li> <p> <b> Perks of the job:</b> </p> <li> 15 vacation days (Subject to increase with more experience in the company)</li> <li> 9 paid holidays observed</li> <li> Competitive dental and medical coverage</li> <li> Casual dress code encouraged</li>;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/sales/claims-representative-a1dc15
e359cc;02/08/2020 00:30:00;February 15, 2020;Penn National Gaming;Las Vegas, NV;Upper Management;Director of Capital Assets;filter_3;v;director-of-capital-assets-e359cc;v;<h2 class=Mandant></h2><h2 class=Aufgaben></h2><h2 class=Profil><p>  Posted Date  3 months ago (11/15/2019 6:10 PM)   </p> <p>  Job ID   2019-70231   </p> <p>   Casino Property    Penn National Gaming, Inc.   </p> <p>  Position Type   Regular Full-Time   </p> <p>  Category   Accounting/Finance   </p> <h3>Overview</h3> <p> <strong>Don’t just work. Work Happy.</strong> </p> <p> A career in gaming? At Penn National Gaming we think you’ll enjoy an exciting industry, fast-paced days and nights, diverse, enthusiastic co-workers, unlimited growth and support from one of the leaders in the industry. </p> <p> An individual could be successful if they possess the following. </p> <p>  The Director of Capital Assets works with many stakeholder groups to define fixed asset types, assess, plan, and execute recurring reporting needs, provide ad hoc reports, analysis, and forecasts, and review work completed by the Capital Assets accounting team. This individual will have direct oversight over design and construction accounting, as well capital asset accounting. This individual is responsible for building relationships with the other accounting, financial planning and analysis, and operational management groups. This individual must exercise effective communication skills, exhibit strong accounting acumen (inclusive of cost accounting), function effectively working with team members located in different offices throughout the US, and offer suggestions and support for improving practices and processes within a dynamic environment. This individual will report to the Vice President of Accounting and Financial Reporting and will consult often with relevant stakeholders, including CAO, external and internal auditors, as well as to individuals working in other functional or commercial business areas, including but not limited to, treasury, financial planning and analysis and property teams.   </p> <h3>Your daily responsibilities include</h3> <ul><li> Ensure processes are in place for capital approval, adherence to capital budgets and placing assets into service. </li> <li> Review fixed asset addition JE's, disposals and transfers JE's for proper documentation </li> <li> Establish reporting and review procedures for projects underway, and a process for beginning, administering, and closing Design and Construction projects </li> <li> Review asset types with the tax team and ensure the asset types are coded correctly in BNA </li> <li> Maintain depreciation and asset retirements for all fixed assets using BNA (GAAP, Fed, State, No Bonus, E&P) </li> <li> Review reconciliations of the fixed assets balances to the general ledger and approve fixed asset account reconciliations  </li> <li> Ensure compliance with regulatory and financial reporting requirements </li> <li> Review monthly asset account roll-forwards for each book (GAAP, Federal Tax, Federal AMT, State Tax, and E&P), each property, and on a consolidated basis </li> <li> Proactively provide support for internal and external audit requests, sales/use tax audits and other ad hoc reports </li> <li> Review SOX and other controls and ensure processes are in place and operating effectively </li> </ul><h3>To be successful in this position it will require the following skill set</h3> <ul><li> A Bachelor’s degree with a major in Accounting is required, and 3-5 years of progressive work experience is desired, experience in audit public accounting and/or project job cost and/or fixed assets accounting is a plus </li> <li> CPA is preferred </li> <li> Excellent verbal and written communication skills are necessary, complemented by sound administrative skills </li> <li> Advanced proficiency in Microsoft office applications, particularly Excel pivot tables </li> <li> Experience in using querying and reporting tools for ad hoc reporting </li> <li> Ability to work in fast paced environment on multiple assignments with tight deadlines, particularly at quarter ends </li> <li> Able to communicate effectively in both verbal and written formats and present information appropriately based on the target audience. </li> <li> Attentive to details with ability to translate into the “big” picture </li> <li> Individual will need to enjoy working on new challenges </li> </ul><h3>Something to leave you with</h3> <p>Penn National Gaming is more than you may realize. We have properties throughout the United States and Canada and are embarking on an aggressive growth mode. Our departments and areas of opportunity are ideal for just about any skill set. And our company-wide commitment to making sure our guests smile as much as we do means you’ll enjoy a fun working environment.</p> <p><strong> Now that you have read about who we are, here is your opportunity to see what we're about! </strong></p> <p> Sorry the Share function is not working properly at this moment. Please refresh the page and try again later. </p></h2><h2 class=Abschlusstext></h2>;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/upper-management/director-of-capital-assets-e359cc
fdead2;02/09/2020 00:30:00;February 16, 2020;T-Mobile;Las Vegas, NV;Other / General;Sr Engineers, Radio Frequency;filter_3;v;sr-engineers-radio-frequency-fdead2;v;Position summary<br /><br />T-Mobile USA is a leading provider of digital GSM/GPRS, UMTS, and LTE wireless voice and data technology standards. Senior Engineers, Radio Frequency located in Las Vegas, NV will develop end-to-end DAS and Small Cell Solutions.<br /><br /><b>Responsibilities</b><br /> Position duties and responsibilities include, but are not limited to:<br /> <ul><li>Design indoor and outdoor DAS/DRAN solution for venues and high capacity special events by modeling indoor propagation, apply link budget analysis, design standards, traffic analysis and performing site surveys to determine antenna placement and equipment needs.</li><li>Validate radio source installation and passive connectivity from radios to DAS demark using RFDS, iBwave and construction drawings.</li><li>Review and approve final RF design construction documents, PIM Test, Coax Sweep Test and Fiber Sweep Tests to accept a fully and proper functioning DAS/DRAN system.</li><li>Collect data, perform spot coverage testing and/or 911 testing with RF engineering tools for post deployment acceptance testing to ensure requirements are met and the system integrates with the macro network.</li><li>Troubleshoot alarms or performance issues and audit existing system as-builts to ensure system KPIs are acceptable.</li><li>Contribute to the establishment of design standards, identify deal or contract requirements with landlords and third-party providers in conjunction with national and regional engineering and development teams and ensure standards are implemented on a site-by-site basis by engaging with RAN vendors and DAS vendors to determine standards and best practices for features and settings.</li></ul><br /><br /><b>Minimum Qualifications</b><br /> Skill requirements:<br /> <ul><li>(1) Using iBwave to design Distributed Antenna System (DAS) and Small cell solutions.</li><li>(2) Using Ericsson and Nokia Operations Support System (OSS) to access and change Radio parameters, monitor the system, and check alarms.</li><li>(3) Utilizing RF theory for current technologies and Key Performance Index (KPI) stats / counters to analyze and troubleshoot network problems, performing large scale network impacting jobs and utilizing RF propagation principles and antenna theory for new site design, working in a market level setting designing new (macro and in-building) sites, and modifying existing sites with emerging technologies to improve performance.</li><li>(4) Using CommScope, Corning, JMA Teko to change DAS OEM parameters through GUI interfaces.</li><li>(5) Using Spectrum Analyzer to measure the signal levels in a Distributed Antenna System (DAS) and troubleshooting a DAS system.</li><li>(6) Collecting RF data using TEMS, Solutalia WIND, and JDSU and post processing the data using Actix Analyzer, and TEMS investigation to analyze KPIs and network performance.</li></ul> <br />Experience and education requirements:<br /><br />PRIMARY REQUIREMENTS: Master's degree in Electrical Engineering or related, and 3 years of relevant work experience.<br /><br />ALTERNATIVE REQUIREMENTS: Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering or related, and 5 years of relevant work experience.<br /><br />Additional: <br /> <ul><li>Location: Las Vegas, NV</li><li>Employer is not currently sponsoring work visas for this position.</li><li>This position is eligible for the employee referral program.</li></ul> <br />How to apply:<br /> <ul><li>Visit www.tmobile.jobs.</li><li>Create a candidate profile, and apply to requisition number 137305BR.</li></ul><br /><br /><b>Company Profile</b><br /> As America's Un-carrier, T-Mobile USA, Inc. (NASDAQ: TMUS) is redefining the way consumers and businesses buy wireless services through leading product and service innovation. The company's advanced nationwide 4G and 4G LTE network delivers outstanding wireless experiences for customers who are unwilling to compromise on quality and value. Based in Bellevue, Washington, T-Mobile USA. Inc. provides services through its subsidiaries and operates its flagship brands, T-Mobile and Metro by T-Mobile. For more information, please visit http://www.t-mobile.com<br /><br />Applicant Privacy Policy<br /><br />We are committed to maintaining your trust by respecting and protecting your privacy. For more information about how T-Mobile processes the personal data of job applicants, please visit Applicant Privacy Policy.<br /><br /><b>EOE Statement</b><br /> We Take Equal Opportunity Seriously - By Choice. T-Mobile USA, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All decisions concerning the employment relationship will be made without regard to age, race, ethnicity, color, religion, creed, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, national origin, marital status, citizenship status, veteran status, the presence of any physical or mental disability, or any other status or characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law. Discrimination or harassment based upon any of these factors is wholly inconsistent with our Company values and will not be tolerated. Furthermore, such discrimination or harassment may violate federal, state, or local law. - provided by Dice;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/other-general/sr-engineers-radio-frequency-fdead2
