h evacuations if required. Investigates and completes reports concerning the same.  </li> <li>  Verifies and approves all arrests. Apprehends (where appropriate) individuals who are observed to be engaged in criminal activity and detains these individuals until they can be turned over to law enforcement authorities. Acts as company representative to law enforcement authorities.  </li> <li>  Ensures the enforcement of state gaming laws including (but not limited to) the identification and removal of underage persons from the casino floor.  </li> <li>  Responds to verbal and/or physical altercations and applies or directs the appropriate measures to resolve the situation. For physical altercations, applies and/or directs the minimum amount of force necessary to restrain any and all involved.  </li> <li>  Initiates formal evictions of disorderly persons.  </li> <li>  Responds to and/or directs the company response to requests for medical assistance. Provides assistance consistent with company policy and the skill level and certifications of available personnel.  </li> <li>  Coordinates and supervises crowd control for special events.  </li> </ul><p>   ​     <strong>EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE:</strong>  </p> <p>  Minimum 5 years previous experience in similar position within the gaming or hotel industry.   </p> <p>  <b>LICENSES, CERTIFICATIONS OR REGISTRATIONS:</b>  </p> <p>  <b>OTHER PROPERTY SPECIFIC DETAILS:</b>  </p> <p>  <strong>EMPLOYEE BENEFITS INCLUDE: </strong>  </p> <p>  Health, Dental, Vision, 401K, PTO, Employee Discount Network, Meals, Celebrations, Awards and more....  </p> <p>  <b>DISCLAIMER:</b>  </p> <p>  This job posting is intended to describe the general nature of this position. It is not intended to be an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required. Employee benefits may vary by location, position, length of service and employment status.   </p> <p>  Final candidates will be required to complete a drug test and background check. Many positions will require a state gaming license. Affinity Gaming is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, national origin, gender, age, religion, disability, sexual orientation, veteran status, or marital status.   </p> <p> #DirectorSecurity #casinosecurity #securitymanager </p></h2><h2 class=Abschlusstext></h2>;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/upper-management/director-of-security-primm-casinos-d25cde
