ng for a Sales Rep who can thrive in a remote startup environment, is self-motivated and can self-manage. If you feel that you understand what Flipcause does at a high level, you have a passion for the nonprofit community, and you feel comfortable having everyday conversations with clients, then we'd love to connect with you and see if we?re a good fit.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>Headquarters:</strong></div><div>Flipcause is headquartered in Oakland, CA. Although being a remote company helps us to best serve our nonprofit partners, a culture of the community is very important to us. Candidates should be prepared to travel occasionally for routine training and corporate events.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>Benefits:</strong></div><ul><li>100% Premium coverage for Medical/Dental/Vision and 50% dependent coverage.</li><li>401K.</li><li>Annual Raises.</li><li>Paid vacations and PTO.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Compensation:</strong></div><ul><li>$70,000-$75,000 OTE (50,000 Base + Commission)</li><li>Equipment & mobile devices provided.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Target Start Date: </strong>3/16/2020.</div><div><br></div><div><strong>How to Apply:</strong></div><div>Please submit your resume and cover letter to careers@flipcause.com and include the position that you're applying for in the subject line.</div><div><br></div><div>In the body of your email, briefly describe why you would be a great addition to our team and what about Flipcause fits the type of company you're looking to be a part of.</div><div><br></div><div>We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity in our company. We encourage individuals of all personal and professional backgrounds to apply.</div><br><br><ul></ul>;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/sales/nonprofit-tech-sales-rep-3a9f0a
