tegies to realize significant cost savings with         reusability and solve issues of software quality.</li>       <li>Supports the development of strategy, frameworks, best         practices and patterns for the development organization.</li>       <li>Troubleshoot code level problems quickly and efficiently.</li>       <li>Mentor and guide Associate Software Architects, Sr. and         non-Sr. Software engineers.</li>       <li>No reason to repeat,  Sit, Butter Cup, sit,  while at work           leave that at home.</li></ul></ul>   <br />   <strong>     <u>What You ve Got<br /></u></strong>   <ul>     <ul>       <li>Expert level knowledge in Java, J2EE, RDBMS, Linux, HTML and         JavaScript/Typescript skills.</li>       <li>Requires a minimum of 2-3 years  experience acting as an         architect for large enterprise level software projects.</li>       <li>Requires a minimum of 10 years of experience in writing         applications using programming languages like Java, JavaScript, Golang.</li>       <li>Knowledge of Spring, Hibernate, Golang, Angular and build         tools like Jenkins, Maven, Ant will be a plus.</li>       <li>Prior Casino gaming industry experience is preferred.</li>       <li>Knowledge of APM tools like Prometheus/Grafana is preferred.</li>       <li>Requires experience with Enterprise Service Bus designs,         development and implementation.</li>       <li>Requires experience with Micro Service Architecture design,         development and implementation.</li>       <li>Experience in SDLC processes, architectural patterns, and         development frameworks.</li>       <li>Proficiency in modeling environments such as Unified Modeling         Language (UML), and at least one EA modeling tool is also required.</li>       <li>Must have strong analytical and creative problem-solving skills.</li>       <li>Demonstrates an extremely high level of accuracy and attention         to detail.</li>       <li>Must have strong communication skills, able to work         independently and be team oriented.</li>       <li>Bachelor s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a         related field, or its equivalent.</li>       <li>Obtain Nevada Gaming Control Board (NGCB) and/or other gaming         jurisdictions in which we operate.</li>       <li>Just to be clear, no kazoo skills required for this job.</li></ul></ul>   <br />To find more great tech-centric jobs, please visit www.phoenixstaff.com.</div> <div>   <div>     <div>       <p> </p></div></div></div> - provided by Dice;v;jobsinlasvegas.net/engineering-architecture/software-architect-one-link-0432d5
